            <abstract>
              <p>Link-stitch sewing on four sewing stations, i.e. on two pairs of sewing stations.
                Two threads are used. The sewing starts from the upper board.
                The tread is laced through the holes of one sewing station and it enters in the first quire. One end returns in the board in order to lace
                another sewing station. The two ends pass each other and continue the sewing.
                Inside the centrefold of the first quire, for each pair of sewing station, three long stitches and no knots are visible.
                Inside the centrefold of the last quire, for each pair of sewing station, there are three long stitches, one of them with a knot.
              </p>
